𝐖𝐇𝐀𝐓 𝐈 𝐃𝐈𝐒𝐂𝐎𝐕𝐄𝐑𝐄𝐃 𝐅𝐑𝐎𝐌 𝐃𝐎𝐑𝐒𝐂𝐎𝐍 𝐎𝐑𝐀𝐍𝐆𝐄Recently on 8 Feb  the Disease Outbreak Response System Condition (DORSCON) level was raised from yellow to orange.And this caused an outspread PANIC buying of household necessities  food supplies  toiletries..etcQueues to checkout snaked to more than an hour Long...*And the usual scene would be like that of the photo below*And to make matters worse  some unscrupulous vendors even raised prices of common items.𝐁𝐔𝐓 𝐢𝐭 𝐝𝐚𝐰𝐧𝐞𝐝 𝐨𝐧 𝐦𝐞......I’ve seen this scene before......In fact  it happened not too long ago......———In 2017  during the initial boom of the property market  showflats were packed with buyers. Each buyer PANICKING to clinch the “lower / best” prices...It was an ugly scene of Long queues to view the units  less variety of options  and for some... HIGHER PRICES!But fast forward to Today  you walk into most showflats and they are relatively empty....———-Ask yourself this question  𝐖𝐨𝐮𝐥𝐝 𝐲𝐨𝐮 𝐫𝐚𝐭𝐡𝐞𝐫 𝐛𝐮𝐲 𝐰𝐡𝐞𝐧 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐬𝐡𝐨𝐰𝐟𝐥𝐚𝐭 𝐢𝐬 𝐜𝐫𝐨𝐰𝐝𝐞𝐝 𝐨𝐫 𝐞𝐦𝐩𝐭𝐲?𝙄 𝙬𝙤𝙪𝙡𝙙 𝙘𝙝𝙤𝙤𝙨𝙚 “𝙀𝙈𝙋𝙏𝙔”...why?• More CHOICES & VARIETY• Lesser COMPETITION for units• SENSITIVE prices———-I’ve seen too many people make simple mistakes & pitfalls (like above)  which is why I developed a frame to 𝐞𝐦𝐩𝐨𝐰𝐞𝐫 𝐡𝐨𝐦𝐞𝐛𝐮𝐲𝐞𝐫𝐬 & 𝐢𝐧𝐯𝐞𝐬𝐭𝐨𝐫𝐬 𝐭𝐨 𝐦𝐚𝐤𝐞 𝐛𝐞𝐭𝐭𝐞𝐫 𝐢𝐧𝐟𝐨𝐫𝐦 𝐝𝐞𝐜𝐢𝐬𝐢𝐨𝐧𝐬.Click the link below to find out more:https://bit.ly/3btex1ahttps://www.facebook.com/100020429562839/posts/491302008227447/?d=n
